thiru_sundaram wrote:
&gt;
&gt; 1. I start heritrix from my application [ not through commandline ] by
&gt; giving crawl order xml file.
&gt; I want to bring up the UI too. But it seems heritrix brings up the
&gt; UI only if i start through
&gt; command line . Is there a way to bring up the UI by starting it
&gt; through my application & giving a crawl order xml file ?
&gt;






Depends. Here is where GUI is started in Heritrix#main: 
http://crawler.archive.org/xref/org/archive/crawler/Heritrix.html#709.  
Currently, the Heritrix#startEmbeddedWebserver method is protected so 
you need to subclass Heritrix to get at it and invoke from inside your 
application -- unless we make the method public.   Let us know and we&#39;ll 
make the change. 

But this method starts up the embedded Jetty.  Maybe you already have a 
webserver running in your application and you don&#39;t want to start up a 
second one.  In this case, try deploying the 
$HERITRIX_HOME/webapps/admin.war in your webapp container.  As long as 
the rest of Heritrix is on the CLASSPATH, the GUI should be able to find 
running running Heritrix instances whether created by the GUI or by your 
application.


&gt;
&gt; 2. I got that heritrix does not support post request. But i am curious
&gt; to know why.
&gt; Any problem will arise with the post request?
&gt;




See recent posts to list under title &#39;HTTP POST&#39;.


&gt; 3. does it support form submit or only takes links from &lt;a href like
&gt; tags ?
&gt;



You can configure Heritrix to run controlled form submits.  See 6.2.3 
Credentials in the user manual: 
http://crawler.archive.org/articles/user_manual/config.html#submodules.



&gt; 4. does it uses the same session details for every request or does it
&gt; gets new session ?
&gt; Is there way to specify heritrix to clear off session details for
&gt; each request ?
&gt;




Usually it does.  You can disable it.  See &#39;ignore-cookies&#39; setting.


St.Ack




